repository-code: "https://github.com/barryjohnston737/llm-guide"
url: "https://llm-guide-uil6.vercel.app/"
abstract: >-
  An interactive web reference covering transformer architectures, tokenisation,
  context windows, attention, model categories, embeddings and retrieval,
  alignment and fine-tuning, retrieval-augmented generation, and the practical
  model landscape. Includes interactive diagrams, a knowledge quiz and a
  searchable glossary. Designed as a companion to the guidance paper
  "Using AI Safely and Ethically in Research", which covers the governance and
  responsible-use dimension that this tool deliberately does not.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - machine learning education
  - transformers
  - embeddings
  - retrieval-augmented generation
  - interactive learning
